pageContext.claim: “When cars are sent in and they pay no tax, but we're expected to pay 25, 40, 50 percent, and we they pay nothing? I'll be honest with you, it's just not in my DNA.”
pageContext.analysis: Trump gives a distorted picture. The U.S. has a 2.5 percent tax on car imports; 25 percent for pickup trucks. EU countries have a 10 percent tax on car imports. China has a 15 percent tax.
